## 2. Separation of Responsibilities

Reviewed module-by-module for single-responsibility violations.

| Module | Stated Responsibility | Violation Found? | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Selection Engine | Choose symbol/session/timeframe scope | None | Clean boundary; outputs a pure result object |
| Context Snapshot | Capture raw market state at a point in time | None | Should remain a dumb data capture, not an evaluator |
| Structural Validation | Judge structural conditions | None | Single concern |
| Sweep Validation | Judge liquidity-sweep conditions | None | Single concern |
| Market Context | Synthesize structural + sweep findings into context | Watch list | This is a fan-in module. If it starts adding *new* derived judgments (not just aggregating upstream results), it will silently acquire a second responsibility (deriving facts, not just aggregating them). Keep it strictly an aggregator. |
| Strategy Registry | Hold/expose available strategies | None | Pure registry pattern |
| Strategy Context Enrichment | Attach ValidationSummary + metadata to a strategy-ready context | Watch list | Enrichment modules are a classic place where filtering logic creeps in ("only enrich if X"). At v1.0 it appears to be pure attachment — keep it that way. Filtering belongs in the Router or the strategies themselves, never in Enrichment. |
| Strategy Router | Route enriched context to applicable strategies | None, if it only routes | Confirm it does not also *score* or *filter by quality* — that's Arbitration's job. Routing should only ask "is this strategy eligible to run," never "is this strategy's output good." |
| Strategies | Produce a StrategyResult per strategy | None | Correctly isolated — each strategy is a pure function of StrategyContext → StrategyResult |
| Arbitration Engine | Resolve StrategyResult[] into one ArbitrationResult | None | This is correctly the *only* place conflict resolution happens |
| EntryRecommendation Builder | 1:1 passive transform | None (by design, and frozen) | This is the cleanest module in the system — preserve exactly as-is |

**Overall finding:** No genuine single-responsibility violations exist today. Two modules (Market Context, Strategy Context Enrichment) are architecturally *at risk* of scope creep because their names invite "just one more small judgment call here" additions. Recommend documenting these two as **aggregation-only, judgment-free** in code comments/module contracts so future contributors don't quietly turn them into decision points. This is a documentation recommendation, not a redesign.

